<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-538-328  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 538 328.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  June 11 1990 n471 p43(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Erasable optical drives bow. (optical storage devices from PioneerCommunications of America, Laser Magnetic Storage Internationaland Optimem)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sperling, Ed.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Pioneer Communications of America, Laser Magnetic StorageInternational and Optimem announce new 5.25-inch optical diskdrive products.andP;  The products, introduced at Comdex/Spring inAtlanta, GA, can be used with either erasable orwrite-once-read-many media.andP;  The erasable optical disk drivemarket is expected to grow substantially between 1990 and 1994 asstorage alternatives are sought by owners of high-endmicrocomputers, workstations and minicomputers.andP;  Pioneer's opticaldrives will carry an end-user price in the $4,000 range.andP;  TheLaser Magnetic drive will be sold to original equipmentmanufacturers for $2,395.andP;  Pricing information for the Optimemdrive, due at a later date, was not available.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Pioneer Communications of America Inc. (product development)Laser Magnetic Storage International Co. (product development)Optimem Inc. (product development).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentOptical DisksWORMInformation Storage and Retrieval.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>